article.headline: Coleman, Kizer lead way for No. 14 Terps in destruction of Illini
article.linkText: No. 14 Terps pull away in second half, beat Illini
article.story:
CANCUN, Mexico -- Marissa Coleman scored 17 points and Lynetta Kizer added 16 to help Maryland (No. 14 ESPN/USA Today, No. 10 AP) top Illinois 79-52 on Friday night in the Caribbean Challenge.

Kristi Toliver had 11 of her 15 points in the first half as Maryland (6-1) used a 32-9 run to take a 37-12 lead with 3:28 left. Toliver hit two 3-pointers and had a three-point play during the spurt.

Illinois trimmed the deficit to 39-23 at the break, but Maryland started the second half with a 16-4 run to put the game away.

Jenna Smith scored 21 points for Illinois (3-4).
